    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="summary">
                <p>
                    A letter by A.J.Holman &#x26; Co.,Publishers of Bibles, to A.W. Sijthoff, regarding the disappointing sales of Holland Bible Sheets due to the Second Boer War. Holman asks for the most favorable prices for the Bible Sheets and wishes to assure his position as the main American seller.
                </p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        
                        <date when="1901-01-24"> January 24st, 1901.
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            <persName key = "AWSY">Mr. A.W. Sijthoff. </persName>
                        </addrLine>
                        <addrLine>
                            Doezastraat 1, 3 &#x26; 5</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Leiden, Holland</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    <salute>
                        Dear Sir: -
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We have not had much correspondence with you in relation <lb/>
                    to the <title>Holland Bible</title> sheets which we were in the habit of purchasing<lb/>
                    from you, as unfortunately we have not been able to dispose of many.<lb/>
                    The war on your unfortunate countrymen in <placeName>South Africa</placeName> has hurt us<lb/>
                    in a business way, practically ruining our market for the <title>Bible</title>. We<lb/>
                    are willing, however, to continue the sale of the goods here, but<lb/>
                    cannot order out quite as rapidly as we otherwise would have done.<lb/>
                    Owing to the large commissions and long credit given here we shall,<lb/> 
                    if we continue the sale of these bibles, be compelled to ask you for<lb/>
                    your most favorable prices. Will you please quote us your best prices<lb/>
                    for the <title>Holland Bible</title> sheets in lots of 100 at a time.In this <lb/>
                    connection we shall expect the market for <placeName>America</placeName>, as our work will<lb/>
                    probably create some demand for the books, and some of the smaller <lb/>
                    dealers will write you direct in relation to the same, hoping to get <lb/>
                    a better price thereby; this correspondence should be turned over to <lb/>
                    us.<lb/>
                    Probably you have heard from <persName key="HULS">Mr. Hulst.</persName> We have bound his<lb/>
                    <title>Bible</title> sheets for a great many years, and as we have an agent working<lb/><pb/>
                    
                    <persName key= "AWSY">A.W.S </persName> -2- <date when-iso="1-24-01.">1-24-01.</date>
                    up in that territory now, <persName key= "HULS">Mr.Hulst</persName> will probably get inquiries for a <lb/>
                    few <title>Bibles</title>, and we could not continue unless we were assured that the <lb/>
                    orders would not be filled by others.<lb/></p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Awaiting your reply, we are </salute> 
                        <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
                    <signed>A.J.Holman &#x26; Co</signed> 
                    <address><addrLine>{A.J.Holman &#x26; Co.}</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>{Publishers of Bibles, etc.}</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>{No.1222 Arch Street,}</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>{Philadelphia.}</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
